                            Protection of minors
                    








            pom details summary
          

The University of Illinois recognizes a fundamental obligation to protect minors when they are on university premises participating in university programs designed to include minors, or are in the care of university staff. A minor is anyone under 18. If you plan to allow minors in your lab or event, please complete the Protection of Minors Event Form below.  This form must be approved and completed at least 14 days prior to start date of this minor shadowing your lab.
Please send completed Protection of Minors forms to the University of Illinois at Chicago Protection of Minors Coordinator at: uicpom@uic.edu



      What you need to know in less than 5 minutes
    



